title: Rambles with an American,
author: [Jacques, Edward Tyrell]
snippet: We turned back at the foot of the steps leading up to the Borough High Street, and retraced our way to Bankend.

title: Rambles with an American,
author: [Jacques, Edward Tyrell]
snippet: " Very likely ! very likely ! you must try it some day," said Mr. Fairfield, leading the way past the tavern and along Bankend.

title: Rambles with an American,
author: [Jacques, Edward Tyrell]
snippet: Between Horseshoe Alley and the Anchor Tavern, which occupies  the angle that is formed by the juncture of Bankside  and Bankend, there was an unbroken line of brick and mortar.

title: Rambles with an American,
author: [Jacques, Edward Tyrell]
snippet: " There was an alley called Bearsfoot Alley between Horseshoe Alley and the Bankend in James I's time," said my client, when at length we had returned to the embankment ; " it is shown on Rocque's plan, but there is no trace of it now.
